      "content": "thanks for this. it's a good start, but i think it's a bit too brief. the compliance audit actually flagged it for having a \"low density\" of our core values. \n\ncan you expand on this? maybe add a section on conflict resolution or digital communication. just try to make sure the core concepts of respect, boundaries, and professionalism are woven into the advice more thoroughly so the audit doesn't kick it back to me. again, just make sure it still reads like actual training material and not just a repetitive list.",
